;Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.70,0:00:35.42,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Over one third of our planet is frozen,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.46,0:00:38.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and yet, the icy worlds of the Arctic and Antarctic
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.88,0:00:41.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,are as alien to most of us as the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.62,0:00:43.25,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,of another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.54,0:00:48.24,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They are places of superlatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.54,0:00:52.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,From ice caps that hold nearly 80% of our planet's fresh water
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.56,0:00:57.86,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to frozen forests that encircle the entire globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.58,0:01:04.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These are places that feed our imaginations,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.20,0:01:07.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,places that seem to be borrowed from fairy tales.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.90,0:01:12.74,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They're dominated and shaped by the ice...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:17.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,..both by its coming and by its going.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.38,0:01:25.06,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This is our planet's last true wilderness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.36,0:01:29.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and one that is changing just as we're beginning to understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.10,0:01:35.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,In this series, we'll be travelling to all parts of these lonely lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.04,0:01:37.89,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,both north and south,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.93,0:01:41.31,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to witness its wonders perhaps for the last time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.58,0:01:44.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and to discover some extraordinary examples
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.63,0:01:46.90,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,of survival against all the odds,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.09,0:01:49.92,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,as can be found anywhere on the planet.
;Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.33,0:02:10.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,To the Ends of the World
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:16.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The poles are permanently capped with ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.23,0:02:21.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Nowhere is colder, windier or more hostile to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:31.97,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm standing at the North Pole - the very top of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:38.06,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Up here, it's easy to see why the polar regions are so cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.43,0:02:43.40,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun never rises high enough in the sky to warm my back
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.07,0:02:47.29,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and those rays that do strike the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:51.70,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,are mostly reflected back from this great whiteness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.59,0:02:57.85,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But the fundamental problem is that there's no sun here at all
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:02:59.68,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,for half the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:04.68,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The polar winter is unrivalled in its harshness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:07.88,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A night that lasts for months.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:10.69,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the toughest stay,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.79,0:03:14.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,as temperatures plunge to minus 70 degrees centigrade.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.33,0:03:19.56,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, the greatest challenge to life here is not the cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.79,0:03:23.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but the extreme swings between the seasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.35,0:03:27.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,When the sun finally returns,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.52,0:03:30.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,an extraordinary transformation begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.80,0:03:35.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This frozen world begins to melt away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.12,0:03:43.68,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The polar spring brings a brief opportunity for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.34,0:03:49.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,By summer, the sun no longer sets
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:52.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and works its magic for 24 hours a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:04:01.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's a race to breed before the sun departs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.87,0:04:09.54,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,By autumn, all but the hardiest abandon the poles
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.63,0:04:12.21,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and the ice extends its grip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.87,0:04:23.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Land and sea close down for the long, polar winter,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.26,0:04:27.48,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,until, once again, the sun returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:37.40,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's spring in the High Arctic
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:40.78,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and the sun illuminates a giant frozen ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.87,0:04:42.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the first stop on our journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.07,0:04:50.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The most powerful land predator is on the prowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.34,0:05:00.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A male polar bear is searching for a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.15,0:05:07.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Willing females are few and far between
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.03,0:05:10.88,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and the sea ice on which he travels will soon melt and vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.30,0:05:19.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He's running out of time to find a mate in this vast, frozen desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:39.72,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten miles ahead, a single female without cubs -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.07,0:05:42.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,exactly what the male is seeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.64,0:05:49.31,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems to relish her scent, even though she's miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:53.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an exciting prospect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.02,0:05:58.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,She's clearly giving off the right signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:05.73,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He locks onto her tracks, eager not to lose her trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.25,0:06:10.18,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easier to tread in the compacted snow of her footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:13.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This pursuit could last for days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.91,0:06:22.57,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The female eventually comes into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.39,0:06:26.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The search is finally over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.17,0:06:42.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,For the female, only half his weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.35,0:06:45.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,this must be a nerve-racking encounter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.89,0:06:48.47,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The male could kill her if he chooses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:54.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But he has other intentions...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.07,0:06:58.47,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,..and she is ready and willing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.47,0:07:04.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,She leads him to higher ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:13.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that courting polar bears prefer privacy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.73,0:07:16.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,often leaving the sea ice and heading for the hills
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.88,0:07:21.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid the prying eyes of rival males who might disturb them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:27.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Few have witnessed this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.29,0:07:30.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,For the male,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.39,0:07:35.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,his only tender encounter in an otherwise solitary life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.51,0:07:40.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But it doesn't last long -
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:44.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,a rival suitor has also caught the female's scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.22,0:07:51.36,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Courtship has to be put on hold. He must fight for his rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.96,0:08:06.18,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees off this first challenger without injury to either party,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.39,0:08:10.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but bloodier battles are to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.60,0:08:41.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Another battle won, though he has been slightly injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.44,0:08:44.04,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He hurries back to his mate,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.42,0:08:47.52,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but now she seems to have lost her enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.47,0:08:52.76,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Female polar bears are high-maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:10.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Wherever she goes, he will follow,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:12.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,mating with her when she allows
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.15,0:09:14.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and guarding her at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.35,0:09:31.26,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Over the next two weeks, the male sees off many rivals
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:33.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but the battles take their toll on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.12,0:09:41.76,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He is almost spent,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:46.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but he has ensured that no other bears have mated with his female.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.30,0:09:54.53,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for the couple to go their separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:10:00.29,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,She will give birth to his cubs, alone, in nine months' time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.51,0:10:02.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and he may never see her again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:07.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He returns to the frozen ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.71,0:10:11.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,no doubt relieved to resume his solitary ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:13.20,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and just in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:17.12,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The ice beneath his feet will soon be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.47,0:10:23.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Each spring, the Arctic Ocean undergoes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:25.42,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,an extraordinary transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.63,0:10:29.78,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,An area of sea ice the size of Europe melts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.82,0:10:32.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,exposing the rich waters beneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:38.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Short-tailed shearwaters have travelled 10,000 miles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.91,0:10:40.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,from Australia to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.27,0:10:51.80,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,18 million visitors darken the skies,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:55.31,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the largest gathering of sea birds on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.47,0:11:13.73,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Humpback whales have come all the way from the Equator
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.78,0:11:16.44,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to feed in these rich, polar waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.12,0:11:27.31,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Their giant tails are five metres across.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.02,0:11:32.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Simply raising them above the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.18,0:11:34.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,gives the whales enough downward momentum
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:37.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to reach the great swarms of krill and herring below.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.25,0:11:56.21,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The shearwaters follow the giants' lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.55,0:12:18.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,For those who can get here, in summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:22.49,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,these waters provide a feast of epic proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.19,0:12:25.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But the good times will be very short -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.95,0:12:29.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,a problem that faces all life in the polar regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.79,0:12:35.34,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Journeying south across the Arctic Ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.46,0:12:38.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the first land you reach is Greenland,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:40.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the largest island in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:45.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite its name, Greenland is mostly white,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.50,0:12:47.12,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,covered by a giant ice sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.29,0:12:50.12,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,six times the size of the United Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:12:58.14,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,In the middle of the island, the ice is nearly two miles thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.27,0:13:00.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bleak, quiet world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.99,0:13:10.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Sapphire-blue melt lakes are the first sign
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.63,0:13:13.73,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that a dynamic process is underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.95,0:13:19.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Each lake forms in a matter of days,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.71,0:13:24.04,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,expanding until it's miles across and starts to overflow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.31,0:13:29.85,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The spill water then carves its way through the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.93,0:13:44.70,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The water courses through an icy delta
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.74,0:13:48.34,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,like blood along the arteries of a cold-blooded monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.23,0:13:51.57,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,a monster that is stirring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.71,0:14:08.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,And without warning, the water suddenly plunges down an open shaft,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.87,0:14:12.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,falling a vertical mile into the heart of the ice sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.15,0:14:40.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This meltwater has a surprising effect -
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.94,0:14:42.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,it lubricates the junction
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.71,0:14:45.54,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,between the ice and the rock floor beneath,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.81,0:14:49.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,so the entire ice sheet is now on the move,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.89,0:14:52.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,sliding downhill into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:58.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This, Jakobshavn Isbrae,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.07,0:15:00.84,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,is the fastest-flowing glacier on our planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:03.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,moving as much as 40 metres a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.91,0:15:11.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,As it advances, it destroys everything in its path,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.31,0:15:14.94,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,even cutting its way through Greenland's great mountain ranges
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:17.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,on its drive downwards towards the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:22.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,When speeded up,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:26.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,these solid rivers of ice seem to flow just like liquid rivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.51,0:15:35.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the titanic force
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.67,0:15:39.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that cuts down mountains and levels the surface of continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:16:02.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The ice is now entering the last stage of its descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:06.01,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,As it gains speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.04,0:16:09.97,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,huge crevasses open that extend down to its very core.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.83,0:16:17.14,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's reached the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.18,0:16:21.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and millions of tonnes of ice have lost the support of their rocky bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.67,0:16:27.53,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Something must give.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.24,0:16:52.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These icefalls are an ominous sign of what is about to happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.79,0:16:56.70,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,..a rupture deep within the glacier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:26.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A colossal iceberg is born.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.23,0:17:53.13,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This single block of ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.19,0:17:55.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,many hundreds of metres across,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.30,0:17:58.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,would dwarf the biggest of mankind's buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.67,0:18:08.80,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, tens of thousands of icebergs
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.82,0:18:11.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,are spawned by Greenland's glaciers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.63,0:18:13.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and their number is steadily increasing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.83,0:18:16.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,as the climate continues to warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.27,0:18:30.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The break-up of the bergs fills the bays of the Arctic
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.73,0:18:33.01,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,with exquisite ice sculptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.02,0:18:39.37,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It also releases great volumes of cold, fresh water into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:46.00,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Greenland's meltwater influences the course of the ocean currents,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.11,0:18:50.47,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,which, in turn, has an effect on the weather around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:02.84,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The Arctic is closer to home than many of us realise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.23,0:19:06.69,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It includes the northernmost parts of the three continents
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.73,0:19:11.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,on which most of us live - Europe, Asia and North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.40,0:19:17.78,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The first bare land we reach on our journey south
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.91,0:19:21.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,is a bleak treeless wilderness known as tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.29,0:19:27.37,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Each spring, animals travel up from the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:29.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to be ready for the rich grazing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.62,0:19:32.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that will be unveiled by the spring melt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.75,0:19:36.09,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,For the caribou, the timing is critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.14,0:19:38.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrive early and a winter storm could kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.23,0:19:42.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Delay too long and you may fail to lay down the fat
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:44.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,needed to survive a polar winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:55.65,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Further south still,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.79,0:20:00.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and stooped, shrouded figures end the flat monotony of the tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.51,0:20:08.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the tree line, the first place on our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.07,0:20:10.54,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,with sufficient warmth and liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.58,0:20:12.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to enable a tree to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.80,0:20:17.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Surviving here is so crushingly difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.59,0:20:20.20,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that it can take hundreds of years for a seedling
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.24,0:20:22.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to grow into a stunted shrub.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.44,0:20:33.17,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But even small trees
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.43,0:20:35.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,can provide cover for a predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.40,0:20:40.47,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Wolves. These, in northern Canada,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:43.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,are the largest and most powerful in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.19,0:20:45.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and they are setting out to hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.60,0:20:51.85,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The pack is 25 strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.99,0:20:55.23,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,a sign that the prey they are seeking is formidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.98,0:21:07.06,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These bison are even bigger than their southern cousins
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.09,0:21:09.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and the largest land animals in North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:13.96,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,For generations, wolves and bison here
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:16.56,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,have been shaped by their battles with each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:19.92,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,making each the most impressive of its kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.18,0:21:25.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The bison will not stay long among the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.39,0:21:27.18,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not safe here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:35.29,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolves are closing in,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.49,0:21:38.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but their chance of ambushing the bison in the woods has passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.18,0:21:43.01,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Their prey are now in the open and grouped together for safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.38,0:21:48.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolves will need to work as a team
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.04,0:21:50.40,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,if they are to make a kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.17,0:21:58.13,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They circle the herd, trying to unsettle it and split it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:00.48,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But the bison are armed and dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.73,0:22:03.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They will be safe as long as they stick together.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.66,0:22:12.24,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolves up their game, harrying the herd,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.29,0:22:14.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,a ploy to trigger a stampede
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.14,0:22:16.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and split away one of the smaller ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:22.13,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The bison form a defensive circle around their young,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.17,0:22:23.78,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,horns pointing outwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.54,0:22:33.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolves need a bison to break rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.67,0:22:43.31,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But the tables are turning and now the wolves have to retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.87,0:22:49.89,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The pack focus their attention on the rear of the herd
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.95,0:22:51.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and the bison begin to panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.83,0:23:29.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A young bison falls behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.15,0:23:37.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Even this yearling dwarfs the wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.01,0:23:49.34,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Running head-down, the herd's only thought is escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.92,0:23:57.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A stroke of luck for the wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.33,0:24:13.45,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The kill will feed the pack for several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.83,0:24:16.74,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But then they will have to resume the chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.26,0:24:19.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,At the frozen ends of our planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.49,0:24:22.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the struggle for survival never eases.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.12,0:24:36.48,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,South of the tree line, the winters are shorter,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.52,0:24:41.73,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,so trees grow faster and taller and forests begin to appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.25,0:24:47.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,As the warm, humid air from the south meets the cold, arctic air,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.76,0:24:53.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the moisture it carries crystallises and snowflakes fall from the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.03,0:25:00.70,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Each crystal forms around a particle of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.39,0:25:08.69,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,All have a six-fold symmetry
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.73,0:25:12.69,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but no two have ever been found with exactly the same shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.87,0:25:24.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Their variety and complexity is breathtaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.01,0:25:34.16,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Each snowflake is water waiting to be released in spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.91,0:25:39.49,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,For this reason, snow is the lifeblood of these silent forests
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.68,0:25:43.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and all that live here depend on it in one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.35,0:25:56.28,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Some, like the great grey owl, appear in spring for the boom times,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.46,0:25:58.89,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,then vanish like phantoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.03,0:26:04.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Others, like their lemming prey,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.31,0:26:06.93,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,are here year-round beneath the snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.97,0:26:09.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,insulated from the cold air above.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.57,0:26:33.21,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The northern forests are a crossroads
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.24,0:26:36.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,for seasonal visitors and arctic specialists.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.95,0:26:40.01,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But they are so much more than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.04,0:26:44.45,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Together, they make up the taiga, an unbroken belt of forest
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.51,0:26:47.73,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that stretches 7,000 miles around our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.91,0:26:51.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and contains one third of all the trees on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.01,0:27:06.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The taiga forest marks the end of our journey through the Arctic,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.21,0:27:10.54,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,from the frozen ocean down across the lands that surround it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.06,0:27:24.52,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The other end of our planet, the Antarctic, is starkly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.71,0:27:28.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A frozen continent completely surrounded by ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.60,0:27:32.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Icebergs here are so large
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.95,0:27:35.16,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that they're measured in miles not metres.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.55,0:27:39.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They're the only obstacles in the path of giant waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.95,0:27:43.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,which circle around the continent unchecked by other lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.51,0:28:01.93,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These seas may be cold and storm-racked
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.14,0:28:04.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but they're bursting with life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.83,0:28:35.93,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,No bird is more at home in water
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.42,0:28:38.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and they are masterful surfers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.64,0:28:48.26,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Penguins are found only in the Southern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.26,0:28:52.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't fly, but they don't need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.97,0:28:55.33,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no polar bears here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.72,0:29:06.08,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These are Gentoo Penguins.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.62,0:29:10.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Each spring, they come ashore to lay their eggs and rear their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.07,0:29:13.61,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Their hungry chicks demand so much seafood
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.64,0:29:15.97,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that both parents have to go fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.21,0:29:24.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,And fishing can be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.07,0:29:42.21,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A southern sea lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.35,0:29:51.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It uses the speed of a breaking wave to catch up with the Gentoos.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.17,0:30:08.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Sea lions normally eat fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.02,0:30:11.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,so he's used to catching streamlined swimmers,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.66,0:30:15.74,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Gentoos seem more than his match out at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.99,0:30:17.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He must change tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.69,0:30:25.48,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it will be easier in the shallows.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.53,0:30:51.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But no! It seems penguins are uncatchable in water.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.63,0:30:59.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,How about on land?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.51,0:31:04.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The penguin's wings, so powerful for swimming,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.19,0:31:06.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,are of no help when it comes to running.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.87,0:31:09.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, surely, the sea lion has a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.63,0:31:18.22,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But on the beach, both are like fish out of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.93,0:31:45.34,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Rarely do hunter and hunted play their roles with so little skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.55,0:31:47.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The outcome is anyone's guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.03,0:32:25.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Every summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.03,0:32:29.78,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,over 40 million penguins take to the Southern Ocean to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.49,0:32:38.40,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They're joined by thousands of whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.44,0:32:40.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Minkes are the most numerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.96,0:32:46.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They all come here to harvest the richest ocean on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.63,0:32:54.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Carrying on south, we get our first glimpse of the frozen continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.42,0:33:14.08,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Southern humpbacks, after travelling 4,000 miles from the equator,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.31,0:33:17.06,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,are finally arriving in Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.05,0:33:25.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Humans have long felt the lure of this mysterious world,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.16,0:33:28.42,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,yet it was only a hundred years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.46,0:33:30.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that the first explorers walked inland
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.24,0:33:36.85,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and were confronted by the highest, driest and coldest territory on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.88,0:33:44.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, the continent is transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.99,0:33:48.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,as the sea ice that surrounds it begins to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.39,0:34:01.34,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This melt halves the size of Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.87,0:34:06.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the most spectacular seasonal change
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.13,0:34:09.31,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,occurring anywhere on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.71,0:34:16.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The remnants of the sea ice are occupied by sunbathing seals
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.71,0:34:18.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that have been here all winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.89,0:34:25.23,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But new arrivals are following the retreating ice edge
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.82,0:34:28.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and they have come here to hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.56,0:34:39.20,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Killer whales, the ocean's top predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.43,0:34:41.98,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Killers are like wolves,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.05,0:34:45.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,for they will hunt animals far larger than themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.49,0:34:49.18,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But even smaller prey are a problem if you can't reach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.89,0:34:57.36,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The solution is teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.95,0:35:03.76,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Swimming in perfect formation, they flick their tails in unison
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.80,0:35:06.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and create a wave that cracks the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.89,0:35:17.22,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They regroup and assess the damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.23,0:35:20.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A more powerful wave is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.67,0:35:27.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The ice floe is breaking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.95,0:35:33.17,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Now they are close enough to get a good look at their target.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.63,0:35:37.36,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The seal is a crabeater, sharp-toothed and feisty.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.87,0:35:39.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Not their favourite.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.23,0:35:47.20,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The wolves of the sea move on in search of easier quarry.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.18,0:35:54.38,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A Weddell seal. That's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.89,0:35:58.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These are more docile and easier to tackle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.35,0:36:05.28,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The pod stays close together and travels silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.82,0:36:10.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, they unleash a far more powerful wave,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.19,0:36:13.37,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and with astonishing accuracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.71,0:36:23.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These big waves are not intended to break the ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.71,0:36:25.86,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but to knock the prey into the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.17,0:36:27.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and they rarely fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.34,0:37:15.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The seal is now where the killers want it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.80,0:37:20.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but the hunt is far from over.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.14,0:37:24.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They need to grab their prey by the tail
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.40,0:37:26.76,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,while avoiding its snapping jaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.39,0:37:31.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Only then will they be able to pull it down and drown it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.89,0:37:39.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Sideswipes create violent underwater turbulence, a new tactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.06,0:37:51.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Blowing bubbles gives cover for others to lunge at the seal's tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.73,0:38:03.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, the seal manages to reach a tiny ice floe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.59,0:38:10.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The killers could easily grab it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.83,0:38:13.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but now this seems to have become a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.93,0:38:19.41,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The seal's life hangs on a roll of the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.50,0:38:35.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet again, the pod joins forces to dislodge the seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.19,0:38:55.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The seal sees a chance to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.01,0:39:04.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Exhausted, it no longer has the energy to pull itself to safety
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.05,0:39:07.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and the killers are moving in.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.03,0:39:17.65,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Game over.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.65,0:39:32.16,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Although such team hunts are rarely seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.72,0:39:35.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,scientists believe they may be the most complex
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.59,0:39:38.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,ever documented in the natural world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.52,0:39:41.36,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They were first witnessed by Captain Scott and his men
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.56,0:39:45.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,when they came to explore Antarctica 100 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.20,0:39:53.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Journeying further south, the fragmenting ice is replaced
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.18,0:39:57.30,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,by a permanent sheet that doesn't melt even at the height of summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.31,0:40:02.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a barrier that many creatures find impassable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.28,0:40:08.02,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It repels even powerful minke whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.46,0:40:09.64,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They have to turn back
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.66,0:40:12.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,if they can no longer reach the air they need to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.05,0:40:25.80,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the ice, life has to be extremely specialised to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.82,0:40:32.46,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Few of us will ever experience this strangely-still world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.85,0:40:35.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and, as yet, no-one knows much about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.11,0:40:44.05,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The crystalline surface of the ice stalactites
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.22,0:40:48.89,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,provides a home for ice fish whose bodies are full of anti-freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.87,0:40:56.90,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The ceiling of ice shields those living below it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.00,0:41:00.53,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,from the violent polar weather that rages above.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.92,0:41:04.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Little here has changed for millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.63,0:41:12.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The cold allows animals to grow very slowly and become giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.56,0:41:32.78,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,A relative of the woodlouse is the size of a dinner plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.23,0:41:39.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,And this so-called "sea spider" has legs that span half a metre.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.69,0:41:46.38,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Now explorers are revealing other worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.42,0:41:49.56,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that lie hidden beneath the ice on land.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.86,0:41:57.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These smoking towers are the gateway to a network of caves.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.63,0:42:04.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Each contains an extraordinary assembly of ice crystals,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.55,0:42:06.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,unlike any other on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.59,0:42:18.61,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Like snowflakes, every crystal is unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.57,0:42:22.72,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Some are taller than a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.69,0:42:27.92,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Others are thought to harbour life,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.07,0:42:32.98,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,seeded by strange bacteria that thrive in these extreme conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.67,0:42:37.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The breeze that gently sways these crystals
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.87,0:42:40.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,is responsible for making them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.12,0:42:43.14,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's steam from the molten heart of Mount Erebus,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.75,0:42:46.66,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the most southerly volcano on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.61,0:43:02.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's now thought that the ice caves fringing this crater
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.11,0:43:06.36,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,may even be a home for hitherto-unknown life forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.31,0:43:14.56,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,From this oasis of warmth at the edge of the continent,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.61,0:43:18.29,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,our journey continues inland towards the South Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.55,0:43:20.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The first great hurdle
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.87,0:43:24.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,is the formidable Transantarctic mountain range.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.10,0:43:30.52,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,We are following the route taken by Scott and Amundsen
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.59,0:43:33.06,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,as they struggled to become the first humans
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.10,0:43:34.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to reach the South Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.83,0:43:41.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They were travelling on foot
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.95,0:43:43.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and their first sight of these mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.86,0:43:45.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,must have been daunting indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.63,0:43:49.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of them stretched one of the world's longest ranges,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.02,0:43:54.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,spanning 2,000 miles from one side of the continent to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.19,0:44:00.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The winds up here are the fastest on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.93,0:44:03.49,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They reach speeds of 200 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.31,0:44:11.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,An ice-capped mountain bears the scars of the gales,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.31,0:44:14.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,bizarre sculptures carved from solid ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.95,0:44:28.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not only the ice that yields.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.98,0:44:33.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This sculptured spire is the remnant of a mountain,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.73,0:44:37.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,eroded from all sides by the ferocious elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.90,0:44:46.22,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond, a wholly unexpected landscape - the dry valleys.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.89,0:44:56.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Only 1% of Antarctica is free of ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.15,0:44:59.23,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and most of that bare rock is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.72,0:45:09.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dry Valleys are more like the surface of Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.71,0:45:12.00,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,than is any other place on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.55,0:45:24.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The floor is covered with extraordinary natural sculptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.71,0:45:29.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,created by the same winds that help to keep these valleys free of snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.87,0:45:37.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Over time, entire boulders are weathered from the inside out,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.03,0:45:39.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,until just a shell remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.44,0:45:48.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,At the head of these valleys, the ice is making a breakthrough.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.42,0:45:56.37,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Millions of tons are tumbling in slow motion into the valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.74,0:46:11.53,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,These ice blocks are the size of skyscrapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.51,0:46:21.53,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the Beardmore Glacier,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.63,0:46:25.94,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,which Scott and his men somehow traversed on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.38,0:46:31.75,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over 100 miles long
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.75,0:46:34.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and one of the largest glaciers on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.02,0:46:43.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,But nothing could have prepared those early explorers
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.62,0:46:45.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,for what they were about to encounter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.72,0:46:57.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The Antarctic ice cap, the largest expanse of ice on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.26,0:47:01.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's three miles thick in places
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.35,0:47:06.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and imprisons 70% of the world's fresh water.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.80,0:47:12.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,From here to the South Pole 700 miles away,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.19,0:47:15.54,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,there is nothing but ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.14,0:47:30.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm at the South Pole at the end of my journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.71,0:47:35.53,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it's midsummer, the temperature here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.57,0:47:39.78,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,is a bone-chilling 35 degrees below freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.94,0:47:43.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's exactly a hundred years almost to the day
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.90,0:47:47.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,that the first human beings stood right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.48,0:47:49.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Amundsen followed by Scott.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.94,0:47:53.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,In those days, reaching the poles
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.98,0:47:58.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,was regarded as the ultimate in human endeavour and endurance,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.02,0:48:01.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and a source of great national pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.79,0:48:07.33,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, the polar regions have a rather different significance,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.84,0:48:12.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,because now we've come to understand that what happens here
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.03,0:48:15.76,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and in the north affects every one of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.03,0:48:19.32,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,no matter where we live on this planet.
;Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.14,0:48:44.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Freeze Frame
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.66,0:48:51.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The greatest challenge for the team making Frozen Planet
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.55,0:48:54.80,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,was the extreme remoteness of their locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.34,0:48:57.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Many of the shoots lasted months at a time
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.63,0:49:00.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and needed a number of crews to join forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.69,0:49:06.86,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,One location that would require such siege tactics
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.90,0:49:10.42,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,was Mount Erebus, Antarctica's most active volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.63,0:49:15.29,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This magical mountain does not give up her secrets easily.
;Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.04,0:49:21.64,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Secrets of the Volcano
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.70,0:49:24.81,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,To capture the full story of Mount Erebus from top to bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.95,0:49:27.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,required four different film crews.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.49,0:49:35.01,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The cave team is dropped off at 12,000 feet, close to the crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.05,0:49:41.41,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,In howling winds and thin oxygen,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.43,0:49:45.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,their challenge is to find a way into the volcano itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.71,0:49:48.92,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They are venturing into the unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.88,0:49:55.04,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere below are spectacular ice caves, melted out by volcanic steam.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.19,0:49:57.85,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting the team safely underground
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.87,0:50:00.47,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,is a relief for director Chadden Hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.50,0:50:04.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent, it's much warmer down here, it's freezing up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.11,0:50:05.41,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Minus 29.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.50,0:50:08.12,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,With him is cameraman Gavin Thurston.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.43,0:50:12.76,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,You sort of forget being in here, you are actually inside a volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.51,0:50:16.59,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, above us and below us, there's bubbling lava
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.13,0:50:18.93,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and you've got all these gases seeping up through here,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.97,0:50:20.61,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,which is how these caves are made,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.95,0:50:23.40,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,so there's also increased carbon dioxide in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.35,0:50:26.27,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,As the cave team head deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.27,0:50:29.13,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,dangerous volcanic gases make breathing difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.39,0:50:30.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The clock is ticking.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.65,0:50:34.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They will not have long to find the caves of crystals.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.41,0:50:41.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Above ground, the aerial team is pushing for the summit of Erebus.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.08,0:50:47.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Series producer Vanessa Berlowitz directs from the front seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.07,0:50:49.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,while aerial cameraman Michael Kelem
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.47,0:50:51.95,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,controls the camera attached to the nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.07,0:50:54.13,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to be around 14,000 feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.30,0:50:56.72,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,on the performance limits of this aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.95,0:50:59.42,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Any bad weather comes in up there
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.49,0:51:01.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're pretty much screwed, really,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.17,0:51:03.05,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,you've got to get off the mountain fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.23,0:51:06.61,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Above 10,000 feet, the pilot must breathe oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.65,0:51:08.65,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,through a plastic tube in his nostrils.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.17,0:51:13.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Approaching the crater, conditions do not look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.23,0:51:16.13,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, Erebus is belching out steam and gases,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.17,0:51:18.42,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,making flying extremely risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.11,0:51:22.68,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Up here, the air is so thin, the helicopter can't hover
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.72,0:51:24.06,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and must keep moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.66,0:51:28.66,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This is aerial filming at its most extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.24,0:51:32.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They struggle to get a clear view.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.31,0:51:38.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just coming up to 14,000 feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.13,0:51:40.53,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,you can actually look right into the lava lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.05,0:51:45.88,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's looking really good, Mike, just hold that there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.90,0:51:49.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The cameraman captures a rare shot of the molten lava,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.11,0:51:51.03,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's soon obscured again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.31,0:51:57.02,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The volcano is temperamental.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.06,0:51:59.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The team have seized a rare opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.19,0:52:01.14,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to see into its molten heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.70,0:52:04.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,but now they must descend to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.51,0:52:11.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,As the weather closes in above, the cave team are making progress below.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.49,0:52:22.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Christmas Day and the crew are dressed for the occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.53,0:52:27.21,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch my back on these icicles,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.25,0:52:28.92,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to snap that top one off.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.56,0:52:34.33,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,How strong are these pillars of ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.25,0:52:39.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's about... - Round about five...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.49,0:52:42.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,So if I squeeze past, it's not going to snap it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.28,0:52:47.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Gavin is reassured by advice from the scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.55,0:52:55.12,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Ohhh! Gavin!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.82,0:52:57.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.13,0:53:02.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,That's terrible. Oh, look, it fits perfectly, look. Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.42,0:53:09.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunately, these crystals are made of frozen water
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.91,0:53:11.77,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and can grow back in weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.27,0:53:15.35,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got these beautiful, clear, glass-like pillars
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.62,0:53:17.37,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and right next to it, this really delicate...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.42,0:53:20.25,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Look how thin that filament is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.27,0:53:25.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,As the cave team explore deeper,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.43,0:53:27.80,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,each chamber reveals ice crystals
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.85,0:53:31.63,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,more strange and spectacular than the last.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.78,0:53:38.28,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,No-one on the team imagined a single Antarctic mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.32,0:53:40.43,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,could house so many wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.44,0:53:48.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Down at the foot of Mount Erebus, a third crew, the dive team,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.26,0:53:51.04,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,plan to explore the volcano's lower slopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.07,0:53:53.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,which extend beneath the frozen sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.35,0:53:57.56,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,On board is underwater cameraman Hugh Miller.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.67,0:54:00.33,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is, we don't actually know what's under the ice here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.73,0:54:03.21,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,So who knows, it's a bit of an adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.91,0:54:07.10,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Old-fashioned tools still work best.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.51,0:54:09.85,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,First, a hand chisel to create an opening,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.89,0:54:12.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,then a saw to widen the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.62,0:54:17.15,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Ice-diving in the coldest waters on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.15,0:54:19.50,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,should be taken extremely seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.75,0:54:21.65,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,This dive's going to be a lot of things
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.55,0:54:25.23,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and warm is not on that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.71,0:54:30.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Insulated suits will keep them alive under the ice for only 60 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.23,0:54:34.62,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Once the helicopter departs, there's no margin for error.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.19,0:54:42.64,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The dive team begin to explore the lower slopes of Erebus,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.69,0:54:46.23,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,discovering a hidden world rarely seen by humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.78,0:54:52.32,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Patrolling the icy shores of the volcano are killer whales,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.37,0:54:54.51,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the most southerly in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.89,0:54:59.01,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Tracking them from above is the orca team.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.94,0:55:04.44,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They need a helicopter to get ahead of the whales
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.48,0:55:07.23,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,and to land them on the fragile sea ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.35,0:55:12.71,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Cameraman Jamie McPherson must pick his spot carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.91,0:55:14.93,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,His aim is to get the cameras
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.98,0:55:18.91,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,as close to the killer whales as possible without disturbing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.12,0:55:25.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,He uses a film camera to capture the action in slow motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.34,0:55:35.74,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,And the orcas come right by him.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.05,0:55:39.83,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in the extreme cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.83,0:55:43.07,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,a film camera proves to be rugged and reliable...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.69,0:55:46.17,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,provided there's enough film in the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.98,0:55:50.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,- End of the run. - No!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.47,0:55:56.39,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got him coming out, I just didn't get him going back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.06,0:55:59.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.68,0:56:09.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Below the sea ice, the dive team is setting up an underwater studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.43,0:56:12.67,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Using a range of waterproof lights and time-lapse cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.67,0:56:17.20,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,they hope to capture the growth of bizarre underwater ice formations.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:26.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Over the coming weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.29,0:56:29.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,the dive team would go below the ice over 100 times
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.84,0:56:32.11,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,to film the extraordinary secret world
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.11,0:56:34.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,on the lower flanks of Mount Erebus.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.56,0:56:39.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of the ice, the orca team has repositioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.20,0:56:43.72,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Their new goal is to get underwater shots of the whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.39,0:56:47.08,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't dare to get in the water with orcas.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.29,0:56:50.24,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Attaching a camera to a pole is a safer option,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.49,0:56:52.87,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,provided the whales aren't put off by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.11,0:57:01.79,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,No-one is prepared for what happens next.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.21,0:57:04.55,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell her what you just saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.79,0:57:10.42,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire pod arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.43,0:57:30.99,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Eyeball to eyeball,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.99,0:57:34.82,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,this is about as close to killer whales as it's possible to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.22,0:57:39.30,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,By using multiple crews and cameras, the Frozen Planet team
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.34,0:57:43.09,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,have been able to capture the full Erebus story, from the fire
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.13,0:57:47.19,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,at its crater down to the whales that patrol its frozen shores.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.42,0:57:53.06,eng,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite a privilege to feel whale breath on your face.

Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.70,0:00:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的星球有三分之一被冰雪覆盖
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.46,0:00:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而北冰洋和南极洲的冰雪世界
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.88,0:00:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对多数人来说简直跟外星地表
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.62,0:00:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一样奇异
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.54,0:00:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里充满了各种极致
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.54,0:00:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从冰帽里贮藏着地球上80%的淡水
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.56,0:00:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到环绕星球一周的冰冻森林
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.58,0:01:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些地方能引起我们的想象
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.20,0:01:07.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,宛如从童话中借来的一般
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.90,0:01:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们由冰雪主宰和塑造
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无论是因其前进还是后腿
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.38,0:01:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们星球最后的真正荒原
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.36,0:01:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且在我们刚刚开始了解时候 它已经开始变化
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.10,0:01:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在本系列中 我们将前往 这些遍及地球南北的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.04,0:01:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孤寂之地
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.93,0:01:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许是最后一次见证那里的奇观
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.58,0:01:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并且要探索一些地球上
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.63,0:01:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在最为恶劣严酷的环境下
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.09,0:01:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生存的非凡代表
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.33,0:02:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,世界的尽头
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:16.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两极有永久性的冰帽
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.23,0:02:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有哪里更加寒冷刺骨 狂风呼号 更加不利于生命
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.83,0:02:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在在北极 地球的顶部
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么极地如此之冷在此一目了然
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.43,0:02:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太阳从不会升高照暖我的后背
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.07,0:02:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就连到达地表的光线
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也大都被皑皑白雪反射回去了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.59,0:02:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更关键的问题是这里有整整半年
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:02:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不见天日
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,极地的冬季严酷无比
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慢慢长夜绵延数月
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有最坚韧的才会留下
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.79,0:03:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为气温会降到摄氏零下70度
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.33,0:03:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是对生命最大的挑战并非严寒
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.79,0:03:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是季节间的极端变化
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.35,0:03:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当太阳终于回来后
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.52,0:03:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,了不起的变化就开始了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.80,0:03:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰封的世界开始消融
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.12,0:03:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,极地之春为生命带来了短暂的机会
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.34,0:03:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了夏日 太阳不再落下
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整天24小时不断地施展其魔法
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:04:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在是赶在日落前进行繁殖的竞赛
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.87,0:04:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了秋天 除了最坚强的都已离开
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.63,0:04:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰雪的控制开始蔓延
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.87,0:04:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陆地和海洋在漫长的极地冬季里 冰封连接在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.26,0:04:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到太阳再次回归
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.03,0:04:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在是高纬北极地区的春天
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阳光照亮了巨大的冰封海洋
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.87,0:04:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们旅途的第一站
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.07,0:04:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最强有力的陆地掠食者在悄然潜行
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.34,0:05:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这只雄性北极熊正在寻找配偶
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.15,0:05:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有性趣的雌性不多 都相距甚远
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.03,0:05:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它所行走的海冰很快会消融不见
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.30,0:05:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它在这巨大的冰冻荒漠里 寻找配偶的时间所剩无几
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,前面十英里处 有一只没有孩子的单身雌性
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.07,0:05:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正是它所要找的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.64,0:05:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管相距甚远 它好像也很享受雌性的味道
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这可是机会难得
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.02,0:05:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌性给出的信号肯定没错
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它紧随雌性的痕迹 生怕跟丢了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.25,0:06:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,踩着雪地上的脚印会容易些
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这场追逐能够延续好几天
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.91,0:06:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌性逐渐出现在视野里
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.39,0:06:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搜寻终于结束
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.17,0:06:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌性只有雄性一半重
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.35,0:06:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次相遇难免心惊
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.89,0:06:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄性要是愿意完全能够杀死它
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过雄性另有所图
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.07,0:06:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雌性也满心乐意
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.47,0:07:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它带着雄性来到高处
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来求爱中的北极熊很在乎隐私
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.73,0:07:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,经常离开海冰 前往山上
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.88,0:07:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来避开可能会大煞风景的其它雄性
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一幕鲜有人见
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.29,0:07:30.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于雄性
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.39,0:07:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是它独行生涯中少有的温存相遇
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.51,0:07:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过良辰难久
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个竞争者也循味追随而来
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.22,0:07:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢爱只能暂缓 它要用战斗来捍卫
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.96,0:08:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它兵不血刃地赶走了第一个挑战者
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.39,0:08:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过血的洗礼还在后面
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.60,0:08:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再战告捷 不过它也负了轻伤
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.44,0:08:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它赶回意中人身边
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.42,0:08:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过雌性好像已经没了热情
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.47,0:08:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让雌性北极熊满意并非易事
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无论雌性到哪 雄性都会跟随
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.03,0:09:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄性会随雌性心愿与之交配
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.15,0:09:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并且每时每刻都在护卫着它
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.35,0:09:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后来的两周 雄性击败了许多对手
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过战斗也重创了它
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.12,0:09:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它已是强弩之末
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过它确保了 没有其它对手染指这头雌熊
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.30,0:09:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在它俩该分道扬镳了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:10:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,九个月之后 雌熊将独自 生下这头雄性的孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.51,0:10:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而它俩可能再也不会相见
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雄性回到冰封的大海上
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.71,0:10:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,重获单身让它轻松
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也来得及时
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它脚下的冰很快就会消失
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.47,0:10:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年春天 北冰洋都要经历
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一次非凡的变化
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.63,0:10:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,面积相当于欧洲大小的海冰消融
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.82,0:10:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,露出下面富饶的海水
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,短尾剪嘴鸥飞行上万英里
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.91,0:10:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从澳大利亚来到这里
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.27,0:10:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一千八百万鸟儿遮天蔽日
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是地球上最大规模的海鸟聚集
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.47,0:11:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,座头鲸从赤道一路赶来
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.78,0:11:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这富饶的极地海水中大快朵颐
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.12,0:11:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们巨大的尾巴有五米宽
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.02,0:11:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仅仅把尾巴抬出水面
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.18,0:11:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就能给鲸足够的向下动力
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.51,0:11:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到达大群磷虾和鲱鱼所在之处
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.25,0:11:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,剪嘴鸥跟着巨鲸前进
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.55,0:12:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于那些在夏季里赶到此处的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.95,0:12:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片水域的盛宴恢弘壮阔
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.19,0:12:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过美好时光总是短暂
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.95,0:12:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是极地生命要面对的一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.79,0:12:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,穿过北冰洋向南旅行
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.46,0:12:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最先来到的就是格陵兰
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是世界上最大的岛屿
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格陵兰意思虽然是“绿色之地” 其实大部分是白色的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.50,0:12:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖着巨大的冰层
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.29,0:12:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,面积相当于六个英国
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:12:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在岛屿的中间 冰层厚达两英里
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.27,0:13:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里是个荒凉安静的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.99,0:13:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰融化形成的蔚蓝色湖泊是表明
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.63,0:13:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里动态过程的第一个标志
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.95,0:13:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个湖泊的形成仅需几天
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.71,0:13:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很快扩展到数英里宽并且开始溢水
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.31,0:13:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,流出的水在冰上刻出水道
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.93,0:13:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,水流过冰雪的三角洲
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.74,0:13:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如同一个冷血怪物血管里流淌的血
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.23,0:13:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个怪物蠢蠢欲动
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.71,0:14:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有任何先兆 水流突然间冲下一个管道
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.87,0:14:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,垂直落下一英里到达冰层的心脏
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.15,0:14:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种冰融水有一个让人惊奇的效果
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.94,0:14:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在冰层与岩床之间
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.71,0:14:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它起到润滑作用
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.81,0:14:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以现在整个冰层都在移动
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.89,0:14:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,向下滑进大海
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个雅各布港冰川
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.07,0:15:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是地球上移动最快的冰川
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每天能前进40米
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.91,0:15:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当它前进时 一路摧枯拉朽
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.31,0:15:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在滑向大海的路上 甚至切开了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格陵兰岛的巨大山脉
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当高速播放时
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这条固体河流看来与液体河流相仿
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.51,0:15:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这股巨大的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.67,0:15:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够切开了山脉并夷平整个大陆
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.85,0:16:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰川来到了其下降的最后一步
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着其速度的增加
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.04,0:16:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形成巨大的裂缝并延伸到其核心
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.83,0:16:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它到达了大海
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.18,0:16:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数百万吨冰块失去了岩床的支撑
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.67,0:16:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总有承受不住的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.24,0:16:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些落冰正是不祥之兆
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.79,0:16:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰川的深处有了裂痕
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个巨大的冰山诞生了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.23,0:17:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一块巨冰
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.19,0:17:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有几百米宽
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.30,0:17:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让人类最大的建筑也相形见拙
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.67,0:18:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年格陵兰的冰川都会
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.82,0:18:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,产生数万冰山
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.63,0:18:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为气候不断变暖
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.83,0:18:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这一数量在稳步增长
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.27,0:18:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北极的海湾里满是落下的冰山
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.73,0:18:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正如精妙的冰雕一般
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.02,0:18:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也为海洋带来了大量寒冷的淡水
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,格陵兰的融水左右着洋流路线
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.11,0:18:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这反过来对全世界的气候产生影响
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北冰洋离我们的家园之近 是很多人没有意识到的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.23,0:19:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里包含了多数人居住的三大洲--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.73,0:19:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欧洲、亚洲和北美洲--的最北部分
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.40,0:19:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们南行遇到的第一片开阔地
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.91,0:19:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是被称作苔原的无树荒野
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.29,0:19:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年春天 动物们从南面北上
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好去吃到春季冰雪消融后
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.62,0:19:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,露出来的丰饶青草
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.75,0:19:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对于驯鹿 时机至关重要
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.14,0:19:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到得太早可能会死于冬季暴风
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.23,0:19:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,延迟太久又会来不及储存足够脂肪
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来度过极地严冬
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再向南走
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.79,0:20:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白雪覆盖的弓腰雕像 标志着单调的苔原到了尽头
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.51,0:20:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是林木线 是我们途中第一处
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.07,0:20:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有足够温暖和水分的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.58,0:20:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以树木能够在此生长
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.80,0:20:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这里的生存异常艰难
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.59,0:20:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从树苗长到低矮的灌木
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.24,0:20:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就可能要数百年
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.44,0:20:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过就算小树
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.43,0:20:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也能为掠食者提供掩护
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.40,0:20:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北部加拿大的这些狼
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是世界上最强有力的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.19,0:20:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们正准备猎食
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.60,0:20:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这群狼有25头之多
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.99,0:20:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这表明它们的猎物并非易于之辈
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.98,0:21:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些野牛甚至比其南部亲戚都大
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.09,0:21:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是北美最大的陆生生物
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里狼和野牛的世代斗争
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塑造了它们各自的种群
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使得双方都成为同类中的翘楚
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.18,0:21:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,野牛不会在林中逗留过久
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.39,0:21:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里并不安全
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼群在靠近
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.49,0:21:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过在林中伏击野牛的时机已逝
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.18,0:21:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的猎物已经来到了开阔地 并且为求安全聚在了一起
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.38,0:21:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼群若想成功猎杀
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.04,0:21:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就需要团队协作
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.17,0:21:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们绕着牛群试图使其分离
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过野牛武器精良 非常危险
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.73,0:22:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要它们聚在一起就没有危险
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.66,0:22:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼群的攻击升级 开始驱赶牛群
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.29,0:22:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是为了促使野牛奔逃
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.14,0:22:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好把较小的从中隔离
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,牛群将较小的野牛围在中间
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.17,0:22:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,犄角向外进行防御
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.54,0:22:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼群需要有野牛打乱阵型
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.67,0:22:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过整个牛群转了过来 现在狼群只能后撤
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.87,0:22:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狼群将注意力放在牛群的后部
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.95,0:22:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而牛群则开始慌乱
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.83,0:23:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一头年青的野牛被拉下了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.15,0:23:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就连这头牛犊也比狼大上许多
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.01,0:23:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,牛群低头奔跑 一心只想逃跑
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.92,0:23:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幸运眷顾了狼群
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.33,0:24:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次猎杀够整群狼吃上几天
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.83,0:24:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过之后它们还要恢复追逐
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.26,0:24:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我们星球冰冻区的边缘
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.49,0:24:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,生存的挣扎从无休止
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.12,0:24:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,林木线的南段 冬季稍短
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.52,0:24:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,树木长得更快更高 森林开始显现
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.25,0:24:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,南来的暖湿气流遇到北极的冷空气
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.76,0:24:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其湿气结晶 雪花从天而降
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.03,0:25:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每片冰晶都是环绕一粒微尘形成
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.39,0:25:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每一片都呈六边对称
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.73,0:25:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但从未发现过形状完全相同的雪花
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.87,0:25:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们繁多的形态让人惊叹
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.01,0:25:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每朵雪花都是水滴 等待到春天被释放出来
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.91,0:25:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因此是这片寂静森林的生命之血
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.68,0:25:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,此处的生命都以一定方式依靠着雪
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.35,0:25:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一些在春天繁荣季节出现 比如这只乌林鸮
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.46,0:25:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,之后又幽灵般消失
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.03,0:26:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其它的 比如它的猎物旅鼠
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.31,0:26:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,则终年生活在雪下
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.97,0:26:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,靠雪隔开上面的冷空气
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.57,0:26:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,北部森林是季节性访客
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.24,0:26:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与北极区域专家的汇集处
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.95,0:26:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过可不仅于此
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.04,0:26:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们一起构成了不间断的针叶林带
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.51,0:26:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,环绕我们星球一周达七千英里
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.91,0:26:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球上树木的三分之一都在其中
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.01,0:27:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从冰封的海洋到其周围的陆地
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.21,0:27:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,针叶林带是我们北冰洋之旅的终点
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.06,0:27:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地球另一端的南极洲则完全不同
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.71,0:27:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是完全被大洋包围的冰封大陆
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.60,0:27:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的冰山异常巨大
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.95,0:27:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们的测量单位不是米 而是英里
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.55,0:27:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了冰山 巨浪没有其它陆地障碍
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.95,0:27:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,畅通无阻无阻地环绕整个大陆
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.51,0:28:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这片寒冷的海洋也许饱受风暴袭击
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.14,0:28:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但却孕育了无数生命
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.83,0:28:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有那种鸟儿在水中能更加自在
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.42,0:28:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且它们是冲浪大师
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.64,0:28:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,企鹅只有南半球才有
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.26,0:28:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们不会飞 不过也用不着
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.97,0:28:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里没有北极熊
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.72,0:29:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些是巴布亚企鹅
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.62,0:29:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年春天它们上岸产卵并孵育后代
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.07,0:29:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们饥饿的雏鸟要吃很多海鲜
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.64,0:29:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,父母双亲都得下海捕鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.21,0:29:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出海捕鱼会很危险
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.07,0:29:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一头南海狮
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.35,0:29:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它利用海浪的拍击加速追上企鹅
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.17,0:30:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海狮一般吃鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.02,0:30:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对捕捉流线型猎物很熟悉
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.66,0:30:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过巴布亚企鹅在大海里更胜一筹
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.99,0:30:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它必须改变战术
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.69,0:30:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能在浅水里更加容易
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.53,0:30:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可惜不是！ 企鹅在水里似乎是捉不到的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.63,0:30:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那地上又如何呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.51,0:31:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,企鹅的翅膀在游泳时十分有力
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.19,0:31:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跑动时却全无用途
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.87,0:31:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在海狮当然有机会
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.63,0:31:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过上了沙滩 两者都像离水的鱼
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.93,0:31:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猎手和猎物的技术都如此拙劣很罕见
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.55,0:31:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果谁都无法预料
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.03,0:32:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年夏天
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.03,0:32:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,超过四千万只企鹅来到南大洋觅食
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.49,0:32:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加入它们的还有数千头鲸
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.44,0:32:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小须鲸的数量最多
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.96,0:32:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们都到这最丰饶的海洋进行捕猎
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.63,0:32:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续向南 就能远眺那冰封的大陆
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.42,0:33:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,南部座头鲸 从赤道开始游行四千英里
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.31,0:33:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,终于到达了南极洲
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.05,0:33:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很久以来人类就受到 这个神秘世界的诱惑
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.16,0:33:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但直到一百年前
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.46,0:33:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最早的探险者才进入其内陆
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.24,0:33:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,迎接他们的是地球上最高 最干也是最冷的地区
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.88,0:33:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着它周围的海冰开始消失
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.99,0:33:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每年这片大陆都会变化
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.39,0:34:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,消融面积有半个南极洲大
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.87,0:34:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们星球各地季节性变化中
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.13,0:34:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最令人叹为观止的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.71,0:34:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海豹们占领了剩余的海冰来晒太阳
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.71,0:34:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们在这里度过了整个冬天
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.89,0:34:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过猎手也尾随消退的冰缘到来
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.82,0:34:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们是来猎食的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.56,0:34:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们是虎鲸 海洋中的顶级掠食者
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.43,0:34:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虎鲸如同狼群
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.05,0:34:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们会猎食远比自己大的猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.49,0:34:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但够不着的话 连小猎物都是问题
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.89,0:34:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,解决之道就是团队协作
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.95,0:35:03.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们排成整齐队列 一起摆动尾巴
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.80,0:35:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形成的波浪让冰块破裂
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.89,0:35:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们重新集结来观察破坏效果
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.23,0:35:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还需要更有力的波浪
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.67,0:35:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,浮冰已经碎裂
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.95,0:35:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在它们能好好观察一下目标了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.63,0:35:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是食蟹海豹 牙齿锋利而且好斗
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.87,0:35:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不对它们的胃口
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.23,0:35:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海中的狼群继续前进 去寻找容易些的猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.18,0:35:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只威德尔海豹 这好多了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.89,0:35:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们更加温顺 也更容易捕捉
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.35,0:36:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲸群靠在一起悄然前行
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.82,0:36:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次它们形成的波浪有力得多
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.19,0:36:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且异常准确
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.71,0:36:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些大浪不仅用来击碎浮冰
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.71,0:36:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是要把猎物打到水下
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.17,0:36:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们很少失手
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.34,0:37:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海豹现在的位置正合虎鲸之意
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.80,0:37:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过狩猎还远未结束
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.14,0:37:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们需要从尾部抓住猎物
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.40,0:37:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以防被其咬到
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.39,0:37:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有如此才能拉住猎物并将其淹死
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.89,0:37:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,侧划能产生猛烈的水下乱流 这是它们的新战术
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.06,0:37:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吹出气泡来掩护同伴扑向海豹尾部
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.73,0:38:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海豹奋力爬上了一小块浮冰
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.59,0:38:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虎鲸能够轻易地抓住它
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.83,0:38:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是这似乎已经成了一场游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.93,0:38:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海豹的生命全部系与这块浮冰
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.50,0:38:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然而 鲸群再次合力将它推下
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.19,0:38:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海豹看到了逃跑的机会
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.01,0:39:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它精疲力竭 没法把自己拖到安全区
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.05,0:39:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而虎鲸则在靠近
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.03,0:39:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,游戏结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.65,0:39:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样的团队狩猎十分少见
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.72,0:39:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科学家相信这是从自然界记录下的
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.59,0:39:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最复杂的狩猎行为
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.52,0:39:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斯考特船长和他的手下在一百年前
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.56,0:39:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来南极洲探险时最早见证了这一幕
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.20,0:39:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,继续向南 破碎的浮冰变成了
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.18,0:39:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连盛夏也不会消融的永久冰原
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.31,0:40:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这对很多生物来说不可逾越
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.28,0:40:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连有力的小须鲸对这也束手无策
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.46,0:40:09.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为无法呼吸到
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.66,0:40:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须的空气 它们只能忘冰止步
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.05,0:40:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰层下的生命要十分特化才能生存
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.82,0:40:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能体验这宁静奇境的人少之又少
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.85,0:40:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且人们对这里所知甚少
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.11,0:40:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰钟乳的结晶表面
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.22,0:40:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是冰鱼的家 它的身体满是防冻液
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.87,0:40:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顶部的冰层为下面的生命提供庇护
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.00,0:41:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,使其免受极地严酷气候危害
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.92,0:41:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里几百万年都没什么变化
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.63,0:41:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,动物在寒冷中生长极其缓慢 并且成为庞然巨物
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.56,0:41:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,土鳖虫的亲戚能有盘子般大
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.23,0:41:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个被叫做“海蜘蛛”的家伙 腿展开后有半米宽
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.69,0:41:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在探索者开始探索另一个世界
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.42,0:41:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它就在藏在冰雪下面的陆地之上
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.86,0:41:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些烟塔是一个洞穴网络的门户
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.63,0:42:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个都是晶莹剔透的水晶宫
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.55,0:42:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是凡间所在
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.59,0:42:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与雪花一样 每簇冰晶都独一无二
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.57,0:42:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其中一些有一人多高
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.69,0:42:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们认为有一些中含有生命
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.07,0:42:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是在这样极端条件下繁盛的细菌
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.67,0:42:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,微风轻轻地摇曳着这些冰晶
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.87,0:42:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正是它创造了它们
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.12,0:42:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是来自埃里伯斯火山心脏的蒸汽
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.75,0:42:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该火山我们星球上最靠南的火山
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.61,0:43:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们现在认为这火山口边缘的冰洞
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.11,0:43:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能有迄今尚不为人知的生命形态
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.31,0:43:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从这大陆边缘的暖洲开始
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.61,0:43:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们继续向内陆的南极点进发
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.55,0:43:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一个大障碍
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.87,0:43:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是可怕的南极横断山脉
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.10,0:43:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们沿斯考特和阿蒙森的路线前进
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.59,0:43:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们曾为成为最先到达南极点的人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.10,0:43:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而激烈竞争
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.83,0:43:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们是靠步行
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.95,0:43:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们第一眼看到这些山峰之时
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.86,0:43:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定也心生怯意
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.63,0:43:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们面前是世界上最长的山脉之一
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.02,0:43:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跨越两千英里 横亘整个大陆
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.19,0:44:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里的风速世界最高
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.93,0:44:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时速可达200英里
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.31,0:44:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狂风在冰雪覆盖的山峰留下了疤痕
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.31,0:44:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,坚冰被刻成了奇异的冰雕
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.95,0:44:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不仅坚冰为此屈服
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.98,0:44:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这塔尖般的风雕是一座山峰的遗迹
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.73,0:44:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被凶猛的狂风从四周侵蚀而成
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.90,0:44:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,翻越山脉之后是意想不到的景色 干燥的峡谷
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.89,0:44:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,南极大陆只有不到1%没有冰雪覆盖
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.15,0:44:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多数裸露的岩石都在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.72,0:45:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,干峡谷更像火星的地表
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.71,0:45:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是地球上的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.55,0:45:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谷底有许多奇异的自然雕塑
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.71,0:45:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,创造出它们的风也让这里没有冰雪
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.87,0:45:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,经年累月 整块巨石被从中心风化
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.03,0:45:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到只剩外壳
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.44,0:45:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在峡谷的尽头 冰雪终于有所突破
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.42,0:45:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,数百万吨冰雪缓慢地落入山谷
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.74,0:46:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些冰块大小相当于摩天大楼
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.51,0:46:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是比尔德莫尔冰川
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.63,0:46:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,斯考特和他的队员步行穿越这里
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.38,0:46:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它有一百多英里长
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.75,0:46:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是世界上最大的冰川之一
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.02,0:46:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是早期探险者们怎么也无法为
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.62,0:46:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们下面要遇到的做出准备
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.72,0:46:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,南极冰帽 地球上覆盖最广的冰体
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.26,0:47:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些地方厚达三英里
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.35,0:47:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贮藏着地球上70%的淡水
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.80,0:47:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从这里到南极点的七百英里
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.19,0:47:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了冰以外一无所有
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.14,0:47:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我正在南极点 也是旅途的终点
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.71,0:47:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管时值盛夏 这里的气温
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.57,0:47:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仍是刺骨的零下35度
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.94,0:47:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从第一人站在这里到今天
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.90,0:47:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎整整一个世纪
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.48,0:47:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先是阿蒙森 斯考特紧随其后
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.94,0:47:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在当时 到达极点
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.98,0:47:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被认为是人类努力和忍耐的极限
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.02,0:48:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也会成为国家的骄傲
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.79,0:48:07.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在极地区域的重要性大不相同
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.84,0:48:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们今天已经了解了这里
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.03,0:48:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和北极地区对每个人的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.03,0:48:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无论我们居住在何地
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.14,0:48:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雪骨冰神--拍摄花絮
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.66,0:48:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摄制组拍摄冰冻星球最大的挑战
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.55,0:48:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是他们极度偏远的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.34,0:48:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多拍摄延续数月之久
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.63,0:49:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也需要几个小组联合行动
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.69,0:49:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要这样协同作战的一个地点
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.90,0:49:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是埃里伯斯火山 南极洲最活跃的火山
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.63,0:49:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这神奇的山峰不会轻易透露其秘密
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.04,0:49:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火山的秘密
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.70,0:49:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了从山顶到底下拍摄到 埃里伯斯火山的完整故事
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.95,0:49:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就需要四个不同摄制组
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.49,0:49:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰洞组在一万两千英尺高处的 火山口附近降落
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.05,0:49:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,忍受着呼号的狂风和稀薄的氧气
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.43,0:49:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的挑战是如何找到进火山的路
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.71,0:49:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在走进未知
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.88,0:49:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要去这火山蒸汽融化出来的 壮丽冰洞中的某处
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.19,0:49:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摄制组安全抵达地下
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.87,0:50:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让导演柴顿·亨特送了一口气
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.50,0:50:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好极了 下面暖和多了 上面冻死了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.11,0:50:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,零下29度
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.50,0:50:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟他一起的是摄像盖文·瑟斯顿
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.43,0:50:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到这儿就好像忘了自己在火山里了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.51,0:50:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们上面和下面都有熔岩
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.13,0:50:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里有这些蒸汽透出
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.97,0:50:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是冰洞形成的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.95,0:50:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这也导致了这里二氧化碳的增加
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.35,0:50:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随着冰洞组向洞穴深处前进
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.27,0:50:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,危险的火山气体让呼吸变得困难
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.39,0:50:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们的时间不多了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.65,0:50:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们得尽快找到晶莹的冰晶洞穴
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.41,0:50:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在上面 航空组正在努力 靠近埃里伯斯火山山顶
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.08,0:50:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,本系列制片维尼萨·波洛维兹 在前排指挥
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.07,0:50:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同时航空摄像迈克尔·凯尔曼
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.47,0:50:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,操纵附在机鼻上的摄像机
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.07,0:50:54.13,note,,0000,0000,0000,,（飞行员保罗·墨菲）
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.07,0:50:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将到达一万四千尺高度
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.30,0:50:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是这直升机的操作极限
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.95,0:50:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是那里有任何坏天气
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.49,0:51:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们基本就完了 真的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.17,0:51:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们得迅速下山
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.23,0:51:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一万英尺以上 飞行员要通过
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.65,0:51:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连到他鼻孔的塑料管吸氧
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.17,0:51:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在靠近火山口 情况并不乐观
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.23,0:51:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天埃里伯斯火山喷出蒸汽和气体
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.17,0:51:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让飞行有极大风险
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.11,0:51:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里空气太稀薄 直升机不能悬停
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.72,0:51:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,必须不停移动
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.66,0:51:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是航空摄像的最大极限
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.24,0:51:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在努力寻找清晰的视野
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.31,0:51:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们到了一万四千英尺
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.13,0:51:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们能正好看到熔岩湖
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.05,0:51:45.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看来不错 迈克 抓住这图像
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.90,0:51:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摄像师抓拍到了难得一见的熔岩湖
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.11,0:51:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过很快视野又模糊了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.31,0:51:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火山让人捉摸不定
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.06,0:51:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摄制组把握住了鲜有的机会
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.19,0:52:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到了其熔融的心脏
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.70,0:52:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过现在他们要降到安全高度了
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.51,0:52:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上面的坏天气就要来了 但冰洞组有了进展
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.49,0:52:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是圣诞节当日 组员也有所打扮
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.53,0:52:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看这我背上这些冰晶
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.25,0:52:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可不想把上面的撞掉
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.56,0:52:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些冰柱能有多结实？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.25,0:52:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 大概...\N- 直径有5...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.49,0:52:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要是挤过去 应该不会弄断它吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.28,0:52:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,科学家的建议让盖文放心
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.55,0:52:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦！盖文！
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.82,0:52:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.13,0:53:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真糟糕 看 对齐了 看哪
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.42,0:53:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所幸这些晶体是水冰冻而成
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.91,0:53:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几周后就能恢复
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.27,0:53:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些玻璃般的柱子美丽清澈
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.62,0:53:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它旁边这个真是精致
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.42,0:53:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看这丝状物非常纤细
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.27,0:53:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰洞组向深处探索
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.43,0:53:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些冰室里的冰晶
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.85,0:53:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个比一个奇异瑰丽
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.78,0:53:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人能想到一座南极的山
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.32,0:53:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会有这么多奇观
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.44,0:53:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第三个摄制组潜水组则在火山脚下
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.26,0:53:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要去探索火山下面
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.07,0:53:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,延伸到冰海里的底坡
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.35,0:53:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,机上是水下摄像休·米勒
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.67,0:54:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,问题是我们不知道冰下会有什么
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.73,0:54:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁知道呢 这就是探险
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.91,0:54:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老式工具仍然很好用
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.51,0:54:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先用钢钎凿开冰
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.89,0:54:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,之后用钢锯加大开口
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.62,0:54:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在地球最冷的水域冰下潜水
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.15,0:54:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,千万要多加小心
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.75,0:54:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这次潜水里有很多元素
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.55,0:54:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,温暖可不在其中
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.71,0:54:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,绝缘服仅能保证他们 在冰下生存一个小时
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.23,0:54:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直升机飞走后就容不得一丝差错了
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.19,0:54:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,潜水组开始探索埃里伯斯火山底坡
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.69,0:54:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发现了少有人见的隐秘世界
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.78,0:54:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沿着火山冰缘巡弋的的是虎鲸
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.37,0:54:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是世界上最南部的种群
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.89,0:54:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在上面跟踪它们的是观鲸组
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.94,0:55:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要用直升机赶到虎鲸前方
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.48,0:55:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并上到脆弱的海冰之上
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.35,0:55:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摄像杰米·麦克泊森得谨慎选址
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.91,0:55:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的目标是把摄像机
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.98,0:55:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽量架设到离虎鲸近的地方 又不能打扰它们
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.12,0:55:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他用胶片摄像机来捕捉慢动作
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.34,0:55:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虎鲸们就从他身边经过
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.05,0:55:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算在极度严寒之中
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.83,0:55:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,胶片摄像机还是性能可靠
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.69,0:55:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要胶片够用就行
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.98,0:55:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这卷到头了\N- 不！
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.47,0:55:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我刚拍到它出来 没拍到它回去
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.06,0:55:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了！
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.68,0:56:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,潜水组在海冰下建立了一个工作站
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.43,0:56:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们希望利用防水照明和延时摄影
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.67,0:56:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来捕获奇异的水下冰晶形成过程
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接下来的几周
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.29,0:56:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,潜水组将要潜到冰下100多次
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.84,0:56:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来拍摄埃里伯斯火山底部
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.11,0:56:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非凡的冰下神秘世界
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.56,0:56:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在冰上 观鲸组又重新部署了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.20,0:56:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新目标是拍摄虎鲸的水下镜头
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.39,0:56:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们可不敢进到有虎鲸的水里
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.29,0:56:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把摄像机绑到杆子上就安全多了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.49,0:56:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要虎鲸们不受干扰就行
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.11,0:57:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接下来发生的谁也想不到
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.21,0:57:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉她你刚才看到什么了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.79,0:57:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,整群都来了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.43,0:57:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,视线相接
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.99,0:57:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这大概是跟虎鲸的最近距离接触了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.22,0:57:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰冻星球制作团队 通过使用多组成员和摄像机
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.34,0:57:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完整地记录了埃里伯斯火山的故事 从它山口的火焰
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.13,0:57:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到在其冰岸游弋的鲸群
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.42,0:57:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,脸上感到鲸喷出的气息真是荣幸

